The "Peace Relief-2021" joint medical exercise between the Chinese and Vietnamese armies has successfully concluded - Xinhua News Agency.
Xinhua News Agency Hanoi, December 12th (Zhou Na & Teng Huaijin) - On the morning of the 12th, the Chinese participating unit in the "Peace Relief-2021" joint medical exercise between the Chinese and Vietnamese armies safely returned to Guangxi, China, marking the successful completion of this 7-day training mission.
During this joint exercise, the Chinese and Vietnamese armies focused on the important issue of humanitarian medical rescue and closely followed the mission of saving lives and providing medical treatment. They completed joint medical command, joint on-site rescue, and treatment of a large number of casualties based on realistic standards, effectively enhancing the medical support capabilities of both armies.
The results of the exercise were recognized by both the Chinese and Vietnamese armies.
At the end of the exercise, Ruan Xiongsheng, the head of the Vietnamese Exercise Steering Committee and Vice Director General of the Logistics Department of the Vietnamese People's Army, said that through this exercise, Vietnamese military doctors learned about the knowledge of exercise organization and professional activities from Chinese military doctors and also saw the medical and protective equipment of the Chinese side.
The results achieved from the exercise demonstrate the professional abilities of the medical forces of both countries in terms of medical assistance and epidemic prevention and control.
Chen Chunming, the head of the Chinese guidance and coordination team and the deputy director of the health bureau of the Logistics Support Department of the Central Military Commission, said that this exercise is another innovative practice based on the successful joint medical examination activity held in 2018 and has very important milestone significance.
During the exercise, the Chinese People's Liberation Army donated medical protective masks, medical protective suits, rapid nucleic acid testing instruments and other health and epidemic prevention materials to the Vietnamese People's Army.